                            <comment id="41688" author="jay" created="Tue, 10 Jul 2012 22:42:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Jc, thank you for clarifying this. Since layout lock is a part of HSM, I will implement them anyway &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/images/icons/emoticons/wink.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41648" author="jcl" created="Tue, 10 Jul 2012 06:46:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The tests pointed in 1) are not HSM tests (they even do not need hsm feature) but they test:&lt;br/&gt;
1) layout lock&lt;br/&gt;
2) layout generation number&lt;br/&gt;
The tests use the restripe of empty files&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="41606" author="jay" created="Mon, 9 Jul 2012 10:26:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A memo of test cases will be needed to make sure HSM code is working:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. JC: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#patch,sidebyside,897,12,lustre/tests/sanity.sh&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#patch,sidebyside,897,12,lustre/tests/sanity.sh&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2. JC: yes a simple test is to use lfs setstripe and to check the layout generation number increases and the new stripe is the targeted one&lt;br/&gt;
3. Johann: A test case which just assumes that the layout has been invalidated (e.g. by failing the generation comparison) would have been welcomed&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please update this ticket if you think of more test cases, thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
